CERN OPEN HARDWARE LICENCE Version 2 – Permissive

1. Definitions

“Licence” means this CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 – Permissive.

“Documentation” means schematic diagrams, designs, circuit or circuit
board layouts, mechanical drawings, flow charts and descriptive text,
and other explanatory material that is explicitly stated as being made
available under the Licence.

“Product” means either an entire, or any part of, a device, component,
method or process which is manufactured using the Documentation.

2. Applicability

This Licence governs the use, copying, modification, communication and
distribution of the Documentation, and the manufacture and distribution
of Products.

3. Grant of rights

The Licensor grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive,
perpetual licence to use, copy, modify and communicate the
Documentation, and to manufacture, use, sell, offer for sale, import,
export, distribute and otherwise dispose of Products.

4. Source

You are not required to distribute Documentation when distributing
Products.

5. Attribution

You must retain any notices of attribution, copyright or licence in the
Documentation, and reproduce them in a location visible to users of the
Documentation.

6. Warranty and liability

The Documentation and any Product are provided “AS IS”, without
warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to
the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
and non-infringement.

The Licensor shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental,
special, exemplary or consequential damages, including but not limited
to procurement of substitute goods or services, loss of use, data or
profits, or business interruption, however caused and on any theory of
liability, whether in contract, strict liability or tort (including
